RETINA OF THE MIND’S EYE

Player: The aspect of an individual’s personality that engages with the game and measures success in terms of the narrative and the rules.


World: An environment embodying physical properties and constraints inherent to the narrative and rules of the game. (e.g., for a board game, this would be the board itself) . Many video games construct a model of a fictional world with varying degrees of fidelity to the real world, including simulated physics and lighting. Game entities and objectives occupy space in the model, which also constrains their movements. The World may also be thought of as an absolute coordinate system.
