Definitions of Key Entities

Player: The aspect of an individual’s personality that engages with the game and measures success based on the narrative and rules.


World: An environment embodying physical properties and constraints inherent to the narrative and rules. In board games, this is the board itself. In video games, it is often a fictional model with varying fidelity, simulated physics, and lighting that acts as an absolute coordinate system.
