Comparative Case Studies
Literal vs. Formal Posture

Fallout 4 Pip-Boy: Normally, the HUD is a coded overlay in screen space (Formal). However, when the player steps into Power Armor, the HUD becomes a Literal representation of looking out from inside the armor.
+1


Dead Space: The holographic inventory menu literally emanates from Isaac Clarke’s armor. It acts as a light source and moves with him, allowing the player to look over his shoulder to see exactly what the character sees.
+4

Screen Space vs. Camera Space

The Division: An inventory menu appears in a panel anchored to camera space. While it may look like the character is viewing it, the narrative does not support that conclusion; instead, it is a dashboard representation for the player.
